cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing event popularity across different social media platforms. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a likely category as the paper proposes a semantic-aware popularity quantification model and a pairwise event popularity time series alignment model. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible category as the paper leverages Word2Vec and TextRank for the popularity quantification model. 
- cs.SD (Sound) and cs.MM (Multimedia) are less likely categories as they are not directly related to the content of the paper.
